                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-649" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE BROWN</persName>
                  </hi>. I lodge at William Wood's, in Macclesfield-street South. The prisoner lodged in the same house—we slept together—I went to bed on the 10th of March—the prisoner was in bed before me—I took off my waistcoat, and put sixpence and 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in the pocket—the next morning 1 got up at a quarter before seven o'clock—my waistcoat and money were gone—he had got up before me—this is my waistcoat, which had the money in it—there is no money in it now.</p>
